     <img alt="A group of people at the end of the Tugun north path, unable to walk any further due to either being in a wheelchair, or on crutches." src="Images/carousel/diabled.jpg" />
     <h3>
      Disability Projects - Oceanway
     </h3>
     <p>
      Council has a proactive program to ensure that its 36 kilometres oceanway network is accessible to people with disabilities.
      <br />
      The beaches and watercycle infrastructure section of Council has a long-term project which aims to establish the oceanway as an international tourism attraction where people with disabilities can enjoy the Gold Coast coastline.
      <br />
      The project involves constructing wide, even and connecting pathways; upgrading or building accessible facilities such as parking; toilets and viewing platforms; providing accessible outdoor furniture such as picnic tables and water fountains; and improving lighting.
      <br />
      <br />
     </p>
     <p>
      <a class="btn btn-default" target="new" href="http://www.goldcoast.qld.gov.au/disability-projects-oceanway-audit-6048.html">
       Learn More
      </a>
      <br />
     </p>
    </div>
